Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Gilberto Tito Rosales

records.addlTxt: Order for Competency Examination by Department of Health Services signed and filed.  bm

Defendant Gilberto Tito Rosales appeared by phone.  Attorney Maryann Corea appeared by video for Gilberto Tito Rosales.  Prosecuting attorney Gregg Herman appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk:  bm 
Court is advised by the defense there is reason to believe the defendant is not competent to proceed.  Pursuant to Sec. 971.14 (2) Wisconsin Statutes, Court found probable cause and ordered defendant examined by the Forensic Unit.  Order for Examination, signed and filed.   Defendant to report to the Wisconsin Forensic Unit on November 15, 2022 at 11:00 am for evaluation by Dr. Collins.
Doctor's Report Return scheduled for December 16, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Gilberto Tito Rosales appeared by video.  Attorney Maryann Corea appeared by video for Gilberto Tito Rosales. Attorney M. Samir Siddique appeared by video for State of Wisconsin. 
Defense counsel has received some discovery and an offer and requests additional time to review. 
Court ordered case adjourned for status conference in Branch 30.
This case will be heard via Zoom. Zoom meeting information provided to parties.
Status conference scheduled for October 31, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with MAG
No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Gilberto Tito Rosales in court. Attorney Nathan Francis Opland-Dobs in court for Gilberto Tito Rosales.  Prosecuting attorney Catelin Ringersma in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for calendar call. Court vacates stayed warrant.  Defendant appears. Defendant advised that this case is assigned to Judge Richards, Branch 30. Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause. Defendant received a copy of the complaint and was advised of right to counsel and maximum penalties.  Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant. Court reserves Defendant's right to file a substitution of judge pursuant to Sec. 971.20 right to challenge probable cause and to have complaint read until Defendant's next scheduled court appearance. Defendant IS Public Defender eligible. Defendant is ordered to provide the public defender's office with the next court date.  The case is adjourned to Br. 30 for a Pretrial Conference.
Pre-trial conference scheduled for October 4, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant does not appear.  Defense request Court impose and stay a warrant.  State has no objection. Court ordered a bench warrant issued but stayed the issuance until next court date.
Case is adjourned to Out of Custody Court for Calendar Call.

Attorney Dawn Marie Rablin in court.  Thomas Hasle appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Court ordered arrest warrant withdrawn.  Recall issued. For reasons stated on the record.  Calendar call scheduled for September 14, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
COURT ORDERED DEFENDANT REMANDED TO THE COMMISSIONER ON RETURN OF THE ARREST WARRANT.

Defendant Gilberto Tito Rosales not in court.  Alexander James Geocaris appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered an Arrest Warrant to be issued. Upon arrest, defendant is ordered remanded to a commissioner. Court ordered any bail on deposit to be forfeited. Court makes a finding that there is a possible victim identified and stays the forfeiture order with restitution to be determined at close of case.
Summons mailed.  Defendant ordered into room 221 Safety Building on 7/19/22 @ 1p
